OL,3,CPartially destroyed historic Brighton
OL,4,Chotel at risk of 'catastrophic failure'
OL,6,FThe remains of a seafront hotel, which
OL,7,Fwas partially destroyed by a large
OL,8,Ffire, is now at risk of collapse.
OL,10,FThe Royal Albion hotel in Brighton has
OL,11,Fbeen covered in scaffolding but the
OL,12,Fcity council says the structure is at
OL,13,Frisk of 'catastrophic failure'.
OL,15,FIt follows an assessment from a
OL,16,Fstructural engineer working for the
OL,17,Fcontractor on site who was assessing
OL,18,Fthe stability of the building.
